## Template A: HTTPRoute (HTTP/S Web App or API)

Use this when you have an HTTP-based application (web UI, REST API, etc.) that needs external access through the Gateway API.

### Prerequisites

1. Your application is deployed and running in pai-dev, pai-test, or pai-prod
2. You have a ClusterIP Service pointing to your pods

### Step 1: Create your Service (if you don't have one)

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-APP-NAME>
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
spec:
  selector:
    app: <YOUR-APP-NAME>
  ports:
    - name: http
      port: <YOUR-PORT>
      targetPort: <YOUR-PORT>
```

### Step 2: Create the HTTPRoute

```yaml
apiVersion: gateway.networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: HTTPRoute
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-APP-NAME>-route
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
spec:
  parentRefs:
    - name: pai-gateway
      namespace: openshift-ingress
      sectionName: https-dev
      # pai-dev  = https-dev
      # pai-test = https-test
      # pai-prod = https-prod
  hostnames:
    - <YOUR-HOSTNAME>
    # Format: <app-name>.<env>.ocp-ai.calix.local
    # pai-dev  = <app-name>.dev.ocp-ai.calix.local
    # pai-test = <app-name>.test.ocp-ai.calix.local
    # pai-prod = <app-name>.prod.ocp-ai.calix.local
  rules:
    - backendRefs:
        - name: <YOUR-APP-NAME>
          port: <YOUR-PORT>
```

### Step 3: Verify

```bash
# Check route is accepted
oc get httproute <YOUR-APP-NAME>-route -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>

# Test
curl -sk https://<YOUR-HOSTNAME>
```

### EXAMPLE ONLY -- Airflow Web UI in pai-dev

```yaml
apiVersion: gateway.networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: HTTPRoute
metadata:
  name: airflow-route
  namespace: pai-dev
spec:
  parentRefs:
    - name: pai-gateway
      namespace: openshift-ingress
      sectionName: https-dev
  hostnames:
    - airflow-dev.apps.ocp-ai.calix.local
  rules:
    - backendRefs:
        - name: airflow-webserver
          port: 8080
```

