## Template B: LoadBalancer Service (TCP -- Database, Queue)

Use this when you need a dedicated IP for a TCP service like PostgreSQL, Milvus, MinIO S3 API, or Kafka.

### Available IPs

**pai-dev (pai-services-dev: 10.172.194.160-179)**

| IP | Status | Service |
|---|---|---|
| 10.172.194.160 | Allocated | MinIO S3 API |
| 10.172.194.161 | Allocated | Milvus gRPC |
| 10.172.194.162 | Reserved | Kafka |
| 10.172.194.163-179 | Available | 17 IPs |

**pai-test (pai-services-test: 10.172.198.160-179)**

| IP | Status | Service |
|---|---|---|
| 10.172.198.160 | Allocated | MinIO S3 API |
| 10.172.198.161 | Allocated | Milvus gRPC |
| 10.172.198.162 | Reserved | Kafka |
| 10.172.198.163-179 | Available | 17 IPs |

**pai-prod (pai-services-prod: 10.172.202.160-179)**

| IP | Status | Service |
|---|---|---|
| 10.172.202.160 | Allocated | MinIO S3 API |
| 10.172.202.161 | Allocated | Milvus gRPC |
| 10.172.202.162 | Reserved | Kafka |
| 10.172.202.163-179 | Available | 17 IPs |

### Template

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-APP-NAME>-lb
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
  annotations:
    metallb.universe.tf/address-pool: <POOL-NAME>
    # pai-dev  = pai-services-dev
    # pai-test = pai-services-test
    # pai-prod = pai-services-prod
    metallb.universe.tf/loadBalancerIPs: "<YOUR-IP>"
    # Pick an available IP from the table above for your environment
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  ports:
    - name: <PROTOCOL-NAME>
      port: <YOUR-PORT>
      targetPort: <YOUR-PORT>
      protocol: TCP
  selector:
    app: <YOUR-APP-NAME>
```

Do NOT use the `spec.loadBalancerIP` field. Use ONLY the `metallb.universe.tf/loadBalancerIPs` annotation. Using both causes allocation failure.

### Verify

```bash
oc get svc <YOUR-APP-NAME>-lb -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
# EXTERNAL-IP should show your requested IP
# If it shows <pending>, check:
oc describe svc <YOUR-APP-NAME>-lb -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
```

### EXAMPLE ONLY -- PostgreSQL in pai-prod

