## Template E: Persistent Volume Claim (Storage)

Use this to request persistent storage backed by NetApp. The default StorageClass (netapp-app) provisions NFS volumes automatically.

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-APP-NAME>-data
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
  # pai-dev, pai-test, or pai-prod
spec:
  storageClassName: netapp-app   # do not change -- this is the platform default
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany              # NFS supports ReadWriteMany and ReadWriteOnce
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: <SIZE>Gi          # e.g. 10Gi, 50Gi, 100Gi
```

### Verify

```bash
oc get pvc <YOUR-APP-NAME>-data -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
# Should show STATUS: Bound
```

### EXAMPLE ONLY -- 50Gi storage for model artifacts in pai-dev

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: model-artifacts-data
  namespace: pai-dev
spec:
  storageClassName: netapp-app
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 50Gi
```

Using it in your Deployment:

```yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: model-server
  namespace: pai-dev
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: model-server
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: model-server
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: model-server
          image: registry.calix.local/ai/model-server:latest
          ports:
            - containerPort: 8080
          volumeMounts:
            - name: model-data
              mountPath: /data/models
          resources:
            requests:
              cpu: "1"
              memory: "2Gi"
            limits:
              cpu: "4"
              memory: "8Gi"
      volumes:
        - name: model-data
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: model-artifacts-data
```

