## Template G: CNPG PostgreSQL Cluster

The CloudNativePG (CNPG) operator is installed cluster-wide. You can create managed PostgreSQL clusters in your namespace by applying a Cluster CR. The operator handles HA, automated failover, streaming replication, and backups.

### What you get

- Primary + standby architecture with automatic failover
- Streaming replication between instances
- Automated volume management (no StatefulSets)
- Built-in TLS between instances
- Optional backups to MinIO (S3)

### Minimal Cluster (no backups)

```yaml
apiVersion: postgresql.cnpg.io/v1
kind: Cluster
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-DB-NAME>
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
spec:
  instances: 3
  storage:
    storageClass: netapp-app
    size: 50Gi
  bootstrap:
    initdb:
      database: <YOUR-DATABASE>
      owner: <YOUR-DB-USER>
```

This creates a 3-instance HA PostgreSQL cluster. CNPG generates credentials automatically as a Kubernetes secret named `<YOUR-DB-NAME>-app`.

### Cluster with backups to MinIO

```yaml
apiVersion: postgresql.cnpg.io/v1
kind: Cluster
metadata:
  name: <YOUR-DB-NAME>
  namespace: <YOUR-NAMESPACE>
spec:
  instances: 3
  storage:
    storageClass: netapp-app
    size: 50Gi
  bootstrap:
    initdb:
      database: <YOUR-DATABASE>
      owner: <YOUR-DB-USER>
  backup:
    barmanObjectStore:
      destinationPath: s3://cnpg-backups/<YOUR-NAMESPACE>/
      endpointURL: http://minio.<YOUR-NAMESPACE>.svc:9000
      s3Credentials:
        accessKeyId:
          name: minio-credentials
          key: MINIO_ROOT_USER
        secretAccessKey:
          name: minio-credentials
          key: MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD
    retentionPolicy: "30d"
```

### Connecting your application

CNPG creates several services automatically:

| Service | Port | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `<YOUR-DB-NAME>-rw` | 5432 | Read-write (primary) |
| `<YOUR-DB-NAME>-ro` | 5432 | Read-only (replicas) |
| `<YOUR-DB-NAME>-r` | 5432 | Any instance (read) |

Reference in your Deployment:

```yaml
env:
  - name: DATABASE_HOST
    value: "<YOUR-DB-NAME>-rw.<YOUR-NAMESPACE>.svc"
  - name: DATABASE_PORT
    value: "5432"
  - name: DATABASE_NAME
    value: "<YOUR-DATABASE>"
  - name: DATABASE_USER
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: <YOUR-DB-NAME>-app
        key: username
  - name: DATABASE_PASSWORD
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: <YOUR-DB-NAME>-app
        key: password
```

### Verify

```bash
# Check cluster status
oc get cluster <YOUR-DB-NAME> -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>

# Detailed status
oc describe cluster <YOUR-DB-NAME> -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE>

# Check all instances are ready
oc get pods -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE> -l cnpg.io/cluster=<YOUR-DB-NAME>

# Get auto-generated credentials
oc get secret <YOUR-DB-NAME>-app -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE> -o jsonpath='{.data.username}' | base64 -d
oc get secret <YOUR-DB-NAME>-app -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE> -o jsonpath='{.data.password}' | base64 -d

# Connect from a debug pod
oc run pg-test --rm -it --image=postgres:17 --restart=Never -n <YOUR-NAMESPACE> -- \
  psql "host=<YOUR-DB-NAME>-rw port=5432 dbname=<YOUR-DATABASE> user=<YOUR-DB-USER>"
```

### EXAMPLE ONLY -- MLOps application database in pai-dev

```yaml
apiVersion: postgresql.cnpg.io/v1
kind: Cluster
metadata:
  name: mlops-db
  namespace: pai-dev
spec:
  instances: 3
  storage:
    storageClass: netapp-app
    size: 50Gi
  bootstrap:
    initdb:
      database: mlopsdb
      owner: mlops
  backup:
    barmanObjectStore:
      destinationPath: s3://cnpg-backups/pai-dev/
      endpointURL: http://minio.pai-dev.svc:9000
      s3Credentials:
        accessKeyId:
          name: minio-credentials
          key: MINIO_ROOT_USER
        secretAccessKey:
          name: minio-credentials
          key: MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD
    retentionPolicy: "30d"
```

Application connects using:

```yaml
env:
  - name: DATABASE_HOST
    value: "mlops-db-rw.pai-dev.svc"
  - name: DATABASE_PORT
    value: "5432"
  - name: DATABASE_NAME
    value: "mlopsdb"
  - name: DATABASE_USER
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: mlops-db-app
        key: username
  - name: DATABASE_PASSWORD
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: mlops-db-app
        key: password
```

### Things to know

- The operator is cluster-wide -- you do not need to install anything, just create a Cluster CR
- Storage uses `netapp-app` StorageClass (NFS). Each instance gets its own PVC
- CNPG auto-generates credentials as `<cluster-name>-app` secret in your namespace
- Use `-rw` service for writes, `-ro` for read replicas, `-r` for any instance
- Backups to MinIO are optional -- add the `backup` section if needed
- Create the `cnpg-backups` bucket in MinIO before enabling backups
- If you need external access (outside cluster), request a MetalLB IP from infra team (Template B)
- Docs: https://cloudnative-pg.io/documentation/current/

